  "description": "# Divided clock skew problem\n\nA high-speed datapath runs at 2 GHz (500 ps period). A generated clock `clk_div2` runs at half-rate off the main clock. The worst setup violation is -85 ps on `stage1_reg/Q -> stage2_reg/D`, where `stage1_reg` is on `clk` and `stage2_reg` is on `clk_div2`.\n\nBoth clocks come from the same root, but `clk_div2` has an extra divider flop in its generation path. Uncertainty 30 ps.\n\n**Your job:** figure out whether this is a data path problem or a clock network problem.",
  "design": {
    "name": "divclk_domain",
    "cells": [
      { "id": "stage1_reg", "type": "DFFX2", "isSequential": true, "area": 6.2, "pins": [
        { "id": "D", "direction": "in", "capacitance": 0.003 },
        { "id": "Q", "direction": "out" },
        { "id": "CK", "direction": "in", "isClock": true, "capacitance": 0.004 }
      ], "arcs": [
        { "from": "CK", "to": "Q", "delay": 140, "sense": "positive_unate" },
        { "from": "D", "to": "D", "delay": 75, "sense": "non_unate", "check": "setup" },
        { "from": "D", "to": "D", "delay": 30, "sense": "non_unate", "check": "hold" }
      ] },
      { "id": "dp_xor", "type": "XOR2X2", "area": 3.6, "pins": [
        { "id": "A", "direction": "in", "capacitance": 0.003 },
        { "id": "B", "direction": "in", "capacitance": 0.003 },
        { "id": "Y", "direction": "out" }
      ], "arcs": [
        { "from": "A", "to": "Y", "delay": 110, "sense": "non_unate" },
        { "from": "B", "to": "Y", "delay": 112, "sense": "non_unate" }
      ] },
      { "id": "dp_and", "type": "AND2X2", "area": 2.8, "pins": [
        { "id": "A", "direction": "in", "capacitance": 0.003 },
        { "id": "B", "direction": "in", "capacitance": 0.003 },
        { "id": "Y", "direction": "out" }
      ], "arcs": [
        { "from": "A", "to": "Y", "delay": 95, "sense": "positive_unate" },
        { "from": "B", "to": "Y", "delay": 98, "sense": "positive_unate" }
