  "solution": {
    "rootCauseOptions": [
      { "id": "rc1", "label": "Insertion delay of clk_div2 lags clk by ~238 ps (div_flop CK→Q + buffer + wires), so the capture edge at stage2_reg arrives too late relative to launch", "correct": true },
      { "id": "rc2", "label": "The XOR/AND chain in the datapath is too slow", "correct": false },
      { "id": "rc3", "label": "Clock uncertainty is over-budgeted", "correct": false },
      { "id": "rc4", "label": "stage1_reg drive strength is too low", "correct": false }
    ],
    "acceptedFixes": [
      {
        "id": "balance_div_branch",
        "description": "Add matching buffers on the main clk branch to stage1_reg to equalize insertion delays across domains",
        "category": "useful_skew",
        "ppaCost": { "area": 0.04, "power": 0.03, "timing": 0.0 },
        "slackDelta": 0.12
      },
      {
        "id": "size_div_buf",
        "description": "Replace CKBUFX4 with CKBUFX8 and shorten the clk_div2 net to reduce insertion delay",
        "category": "size_up",
        "ppaCost": { "area": 0.02, "power": 0.02, "timing": 0.0 },
        "slackDelta": 0.10
      },
      {
        "id": "set_clock_latency",
        "description": "Apply `set_clock_latency -source 0.1 [get_clocks clk_div2]` to model the generated-clock insertion delay explicitly and give the tool budget",
        "category": "change_constraint",
        "ppaCost": { "area": 0.0, "power": 0.0, "timing": 0.0 },
        "slackDelta": 0.09
      }
    ]
  },
  "hintTree": {
    "nudge": "When the violating path crosses between two related clocks, the first question isn't 'is the data path too slow' — it's something about the clocks themselves.",
    "hint": "Look at the clock network for both `clk` and `clk_div2`. Pay attention to how clk_div2 is generated and how many stages sit between the root clock and stage2_reg/CK.",
    "walkthrough": "`report_clock_network -clock clk` shows stage1_reg gets clk at ~0.095 ns. `report_clock_network -clock clk_div2` shows stage2_reg gets it at ~0.333 ns (clk → div_flop CK→Q 0.16 + net 0.03 + CKBUFX4 0.048 + net 0.025 + the original clk latency 0.08). That 238 ps of extra insertion delay eats the budget. Fix: rebalance the main-clk branch to equalize, or set a source latency so STA knows about the generated-clock delay."
  }
}
